<h3>ARIA Support</h3>
{{#property-text name="role"}}
    This attribute is automatically rendered as <code>role="dialog"</code>
{{/property-text}}

{{#property-text name="aria-hidden"}}
    This attribute is automatically rendered as <code>aria-hidden="true"</code>
{{/property-text}}

{{#property-text name="aria-labelledby"}}
<p> This attribute is automatically rendered as <code>aria-labelledby="X"</code>, where X is a string composed of the value modalTitle- followed by a random number.
If you pass in a title to the <code>sl-modal-header</code> component, no action is needed on your part, the <code>aria-labelledby</code> attribute will automatically point to the id of the title element. If you do not pass in a title and are <em>not</em> using a custom header, the <code>aria-labelledby</code> attribute will not be present.</p>

<p>If you would like to use a custom header you will need to identify a section of text that servers as the label for this dialog and give it the same id value assigned to the <code>aria-labelledby</code> attribute.</p>

<p>The example below illustrates how to bind the value of the <code>ariaLabelledBy</code> property to the id of a target element using <code>id=\{{ariaLabelledBy}}</code>.</p>

<pre>\{{#sl-modal name="labelledbyDemo"}}
    \{{#sl-modal-header as |ariaLabelledBy|}}
        &lt;button class=&quot;close&quot; data-dismiss=&quot;modal&quot; type=&quot;button&quot;&gt;
            &lt;span aria-hidden=&quot;true&quot; class=&quot;fa fa-close&quot;&gt;&lt;/span&gt;
            &lt;span class=&quot;sr-only&quot;&gt;Close&lt;/span&gt;
        &lt;/button&gt;
        &lt;span class=&quot;modal-title&quot; id=\{{ariaLabelledBy}}&gt;Custom Header&lt;/span&gt;
    \{{/sl-modal-header}}

    \{{#sl-modal-body}}
       &lt;p&gt;Modal with a custom header&lt;/p&gt;
    \{{/sl-modal-body}}

    \{{sl-modal-footer}}
\{{/sl-modal}}
</pre>
{{/property-text}}

{{#property-text name="aria-describedby"}}
<p>The <code>ariaDescribedBy</code> property can be set on the <code>sl-modal</code> component. Once this property is set, you will need to provide an element with a section of text whose <code>id</code> attribute corresponds to the <code>ariaDescribedBy</code> property set on the <code>sl-modal</code> component, as shown in the code below.</p>

<pre>\{{#sl-modal name="describedbyDemo" ariaDescribedBy="modalDescription"}}
    \{{#sl-modal-header}}
       &#x3C;span id=&#x22;modalDescription&#x22;&#x3E;A description of the modal&#x3C;/span&#x3E;
    \{{/sl-modal-header}}

    \{{#sl-modal-body}}
       &lt;p&gt;Modal showing describedby usage&lt;/p&gt;
    \{{/sl-modal-body}}

    \{{sl-modal-footer}}
\{{/sl-modal}}
</pre>
{{/property-text}}
